Seeing problems at conda-forge, likely due to this: https://github.com/conda-forge/conda-execute-feedstock/pull/8

The root prefix activate script is getting clobbered (judging by what happens locally on my computer.)

@ajspeck I'm going to fix this now, in the name of urgency.  I'll reference this comment to give you credit for your suggestion.

`distutils.spawn.find_executable` only does half the job of `shutil.which`, i.e., it is only checking for existence but not user executability.
I think (given a `shutil.which` implementation) you'd want something like
```python
if not os.path.dirname(self.involucro_bin):
    return shutil.which(self.involucro_bin)
return (os.access(self.involucro_bin, os.F_OK | os.X_OK) and not os.path.isdir(self.involucro_bin))
```
```

Maybe a better way to do this is to make it consistent with the other customization hooks. Do something like

```py
class WidgetView(GenericModelView):
    api_spec = ModelApiSpec()

    def get(self, id):
        return self.retrieve(id)
```

The idea here is that it'd be nice to separate out the inheritance hierarchy of the view spec generation from that of the views themselves - that way you could have better re-use of custom spec generation across multiple unrelated views as needed.
